{"TopicId":188977,"ForumId":70,"TopicTitle":"Blank altitude meter 1.8","CreatedByName":"Fierce Wolf","CreatedById":200019,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-17T12:44:12Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Fierce Wolf","CreatedById":200019,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-17T12:44:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi everyone, I wanted to know if you had the same issue. After the 1.8 update (and glitches from either \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Environmental Visual Enhancement (mod)\u0022\u003EEVE\u003C/abbr\u003E or Scatterer) my altitude meter shows blank in both sea and ground level. it happens in new ships and already launched.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy best guess (untested): \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003EKER\u003C/abbr\u003E, that is acting weirdly\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Galileo","CreatedById":150430,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-17T14:45:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you adjust the UI scale this happens. Squad is aware, apparently.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fierce Wolf","CreatedById":200019,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-17T22:27:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223688782\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188977\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221571323505\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150430\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Galileo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Galileo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you adjust the UI scale this happens. Squad is aware, apparently.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou were absolutely right. Scalling it to 101% and above fixes the meter. 100 and below shows blank.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Finchy_McFinch","CreatedById":193848,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-24T06:22:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223689113\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188977\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221571351226\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022200019\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Fierce Wolf\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/18/2019 at 8:27 AM, Fierce Wolf said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou were absolutely right. Scalling it to 101% and above fixes the meter. 100 and below shows blank.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there anyway to fix this WITHOUT making everything huge and ugly?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}